      • handleKeyEventForControlOptionsMenu

        private void handleKeyEventForControlOptionsMenu(javafx.event.EventHandler<javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent> keyHandler,
                                                 javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent event,
                                                 int btnIndex,
                                                 javafx.scene.control.Button btn)
        Event handler for the EventHandler (KeyEvent)'s that assigns the KeyCode key pressed to the corresponding KeyCode control key if the user didn't try to use a KeyCode that is already assigned to another KeyCode control key. If the user does try to assign a KeyCode key to a KeyCode control key that is already assigned that KeyCode key, the KeyCode control key is assigned its previous KeyCode key. If successful, that KeyCode key is assigned its corresponding index in the KeyCode[] controlKeys and that KeyCode is assigned to the proper KeyCode control key. Whether it is successful or not, the resulting KeyCode key name is assigned as the text in the corresponding Button.
        Parameters:
        keyHandler - EventHandler (KeyEvent) parameter - The handler this method is executing for
        event - KeyEvent parameter - The KeyCode key that was pressed
        btnIndex - int parameter - The index of the Button in the Button[] buttons
        btn - Button parameter - The Button that was clicked to activate the EventHandler

                       int xCoord,
                       int yCoord,
                       int blockType)
